<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="213" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1312,1442]" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[263,532,1312,1333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karol-marholdii">
<emphasis box="[263,532,1312,1333]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Cardamine karol-marholdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is substantially different for any congener by being small subshrub with strongly flexuous racemes and short-node stems roughened by the persistent, indurated, triangular petiolar bases of cauline leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
