<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,308,159,183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Eponymy:</emphasis>
—The species is named in honor of the eminent Slovak botanist Karol Marhold (
<date box="[1189,1320,158,183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" value="1959-06-01">1 June 1959</date>
–), a staff of the Institute of Botany and academician, Slovak Academy of Sciences (Bratislava), professor in Charles University (
<collectingRegion box="[1369,1447,195,219]" country="Czech Republic" name="Praha" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Prague</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,310,231,255]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
), an outstanding expert on the 
<taxonomicName box="[637,777,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
, and the world authority on the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1185,1304,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1304,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Cardamine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="216" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,319,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[345,642,267,291]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karol-marholdii">
<emphasis box="[345,642,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Cardamine karol-marholdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from all other species of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[1275,1416,267,291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" rank="tribe" tribe="Cardamineae">Cardamineae</taxonomicName>
by its somewhat subshrubby habit and has slender, strongly flexuous, woody stems with persistent, thickened bases of petioles that make the rather rough. It also has curved, pinnatisect leaves with overlapping, appressed, lobes grooved adaxially. All other species of the tribe are annuals or perennials with herbaceous stems straight to slightly flexuous but never roughened by their petiolar bases of caducous cauline leaves. The racemes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[860,1061,411,435]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karol-marholdii">
<emphasis box="[860,1061,411,435]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">C. karol-marholdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are bracteate basally, but unlike the numerous other bracteate species of the genus, the rachis is profoundly flexuous, and the young fruits are puberulent at least along the replum. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[379,498,483,507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[379,498,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Cardamine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accounts of 
<bibRefCitation author="Rollins, R. C." box="[634,790,483,507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" refId="ref1445" refString="Rollins, R. C. (1993) The Cruciferae of Continental North America. Stanford University Press, Stanford, 976 pp." type="book" year="1993">Rollins (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; Lihova, J." box="[840,1104,483,507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" pagination="464 - 484" refId="ref1333" refString="Al-Shehbaz, I. A., Marhold, K. &amp; Lihova, J. (2010) Cardamine. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (eds.) Flora of North America North of Mexico, volume 7. Oxford University Press, New York and Oxford, pp. 464 - 484." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Al-Shehbaz 
<emphasis box="[973,1027,483,507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
do not relate this novelty to any other species, and the only species in all North and Central America with flexuous racemes is the unrelated 
<taxonomicName authority="Brandegee (1906: 233)" authorityName="Brandegee" authorityPageNumber="233" authorityYear="1906" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrocarpa">
<emphasis box="[1290,1451,519,542]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">C. macrocarpa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brandegee, T. S." box="[136,384,555,579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" pagination="231 - 241" refId="ref1392" refString="Brandegee, T. S. (1906) New species of Mexican plants collected by Dr. C. A. Purpus. Zoe 5: 231 - 241." type="journal article" year="1906">Brandegee (1906: 233)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, an annual herb of Texas and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[794,875,555,579]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[889,987,555,579]" country="Mexico" name="Coahuila de Zaragoza" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Coahuila</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1038,1171,555,579]" country="Mexico" name="Nuevo Leon" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Nuevo Leon</collectingRegion>
) with slightly to distinctly flexuous (gyrate sensu Rollins) racemes, 5–9-foliolate cauline leaves with ovate to oblong, repand to dentate or lobed petiolulate leaflets, glabrous fruits 
<quantity box="[510,630,626,650]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" unit="cm" value="3.55" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4.6 cm</quantity>
long, 14–22-ovuled ovaries, and ebracteate racemes. Its southernmost range is well over 1000 air kilometers away from the Mexican state 
<collectingRegion box="[797,880,663,687]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[962,1163,663,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cardamine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karol-marholdii">
<emphasis box="[962,1163,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="216">C. karol-marholdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to grow so far.
</paragraph>
